definition.value: Fusarium is a large genus of filamentous fungi, part of a group often referred to as hyphomycetes, widely distributed in soil and associated with plants.
Fusarium graminearum (teleomorph Gibberella zeae) is a plant pathogen which causes fusarium head blight and affects many cereal crops.
Trichoderma harzianum is fungus widely recognized as a potential biocontrol agent against several soilborne plant pathogens.
